                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/7441: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-06-07T20:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 7, 1926—8 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received June 7—8:25 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>241. My 239, June 3, noon.<note n="95" xml:id="d849fn95">Not printed.</note>
                    Following from American consul general at Canton: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“June 5, noon. Canton regime has appointed Eugene Ch’en, T. V. Soong and
                            Chan Kung-pok to negotiate with Hongkong for the settlement of the
                            strike. Government has ordered also the abolition of the oil monopoly on
                            June 15th, but it is understood high stamp tax will be retained.</p>
                        <p>Office of Provincial Commissioner of Foreign Affairs has been abolished
                            and Ministry of Foreign Affairs will communicate direct with
                            consuls.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
